description:
### Problem

The [documentation](https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/integration/advanced_search/elasticsearch.html#guidance-on-choosing-optimal-cluster-configuration) states to consider the number of documents in the index when determining shard size. During the Elastic consultation, we noticed at least 1 index (Notes) did not follow the guidance (there may be others).


### Proposal

* For each index, follow the [guidance from our documentation](https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/integration/advanced_search/elasticsearch.html#guidance-on-choosing-optimal-cluster-configuration) and change the shard count. 
* Create a change management issue (one or multiple) to address each index and link back to this issue
* In this issue (or change management issue), take captures of before and after Elasticsearch performance to assess impact

#### Index list

* main
  * actual: {- 120 -}
  * expected: {+ 180 +}
* issues
  * actual: {- 20 -}
  * expected: {+ 32 +}
* merge requests
  * actual: {- 5 -}
  * expected: {+ 14 +}
* commits
  * actual: {- 120 -}
  * expected: {+ 180 +}
* notes
  * actual: {- 2 -}
  * expected: {+ 24 +}
